 complex processes of Medieval design and construction. They research structural patterns in the processes involved, analyze building methods, and relate their findings to historic documents. The approach of combining field research with the study of literary sources provides a fresh look at the impressive monuments and shines new light on technological advances and construction technology of the time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aArchitecture, Late GothiczMediterranean Region. 0aArchitecture, MedievalzMediterranean Region. 0aVaults (Architecture), GothiczMediterranean Region. 0aVaults (Architecture), MedievalzMediterranean Region. 7aARCHITECTURE / History / Medieval.2bisacsh1 aDomenge, Joan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuentes, Paula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuentes, Paula, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGarofalo, Emanuela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuerta, Santiago, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNobile, Marco Rosario, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRabasa Díaz, Enrique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReynés, Guillermo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVegas, Fernando, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWendland, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWunderwald, Anke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWunderwald, Anke, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZaragozá, Arturo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe G